"Giorgia Meloni, between nationalists, franchists and friends of Trump, attacks us from Spain saying that the left erases identity. One day he will explain to us - says Schlein - what it means, meanwhile we remind you from Italy that after a year and a half to the government, she is erasing the freedom of people. Because there's no freedom if you're hungry, and you can't pay rent. We are proud of our anti-fascist identity that comes from the Constitution, and we would like you to say the same. Because of the fact that she is a woman, a mother and a Christian - the leader dem concludes - the Italians who cannot bring bread home do nothing".&nbsp;
