AGI -&nbsp; "Take an accurate verification of the damage caused by the flood that struck Milan and the neighboring municipalities and evaluate the adoption of extraordinary measures for affected communities, in order to guarantee immediate assistance to evacuated persons and support to local businesses who suffered economic losses." This is what Members Silvia Roggiani, regional secretary Pd Lombardia and Marco Simiani, group leader Dem in the Environment Commission, in a question addressed to the Minister of the Environment and also signed by the group leader of the Democratic Party Braga and the Members Cuperlo, Forattini, Girelli, Guerini, Mauri, Peluffo and Quartapelle.
<br> "The flood that hit Milan on 15 May last, the neighboring municipalities and much of Lombardy - reads in the text of the question - has caused devastating consequences on the territory, causing serious inconvenience for the resident population and significant damage to infrastructures with isolated inhabited centers, displaced families and inagable roads. The fact that the current emergency situation has already been experienced in Lombardy in recent years and in particular last summer when many extreme events have occurred, highlights the urgency of adopting policies and interventions aimed to effectively prevent and manage the hydrogeological risk and to allocate more resources for this purpose".
&nbsp;
