"But the Meloni Government - the questioners emphasize - practically halved the funds available for contrast to the hydrogeological dissect. The National Resumption and Resilience Plan originally provided €2.49 billion for this measure (mission 2, component 4, investment 2.1) while the new Pnrr cancels € 1,287 billion".
"They are chosen - they conclude the deputies of the Democratic Party - which appear devastating in the light of the continuous episodes of bad weather that are hitting the country."&nbsp;
